				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I recall having read somewhere in the forums someone (Disch? Blargg?) talking about some partial tests done on MMC1 reset state, from which it was told the initial values for the regs are something like
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">Regs&#91; 0 &#93; = 0x0F;<br />Regs&#91; 1 &#93; = Regs&#91; 2 &#93; = Regs&#91; 3 &#93; = 0x1F;</div>
<br />By doing so, several games don't even start running, while using 0x00 for all of them seems to work fine.
<br />
<br />On the SRAM side, ogghh.. it is quite a pain to implement this mapper properly for programs defined by the iNES header, as every MMC1 revision interprets differently every bit of its registers. How do you guys work this problem out in your emus?</div>

